In [102]:
def correlation(dataset, threshold):  #threshold=used to assign a specific predicted class for each object
    col_corr = set()  # define variable that is set only unique feature coming
    corr_matrix = dataset.corr()  #corr_matrix=used to evaluate the relationship between two variables in a data set
    for i in range(len(corr_matrix.columns)):
        for j in range(i):
            if abs(corr_matrix.iloc[i, j]) > threshold:  #abs=returns the absolute value of the expression value
                colname = corr_matrix.columns[i]
                col_corr.add(colname)
    return col_corr
